    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-07-19</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-10-22T19:39:47Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Veteran's Choice in Nursing Home Care Act - Allows the Secretary of Veterans Affairs to enter into agreements with non-Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) nursing homes of the veteran's choice to provide nursing home care to veterans eligible for such care through the VA. Requires the: (1) Secretary to pay the non-VA facility for the provision of such care, with payment limits; and (2) veteran who requests such care to assume responsibility for costs that exceeds the VA limits.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Veteran's Choice in Nursing Home Care Act</title>
    <titles>
      <item>
        <titleType>Official Title as Introduced</titleType>
        <title>To amend title 38, United States Code, to direct the Secretary of Veterans Affairs to provide partial payment for nursing home care to eligible veterans at a non-Department of Veterans Affairs nursing home of the veteran's choice, and for other purposes.</title>
